es.fnl.fsm
Class ExactMatcher<E>

java.lang.Object
  es.fnl.fsm.ExactMatcher<E>

public class ExactMatcher<E>
extends Object

A generic DFA for doing exact pattern matching. The implementation is based on the classical Knuth-Morris-Pratt algorithm to search for an exact, sequential pattern.

This is an exact matcher, so elements are compared using equals(Object). Note that the empty pattern is illegal, while a null in the pattern is allowed to match a null in the sequence if at the right position.

Author:
Florian Leitner
